+### 2026-05-10 10:07 UTC — CV of daughter cluster size: U-shaped prediction [REMOTE HEARTBEAT #16 — Bones]
+
+**Question:** Is the CV of daughter cluster size monotonically increasing with entanglement density, or U-shaped — minimal at an intermediate entanglement level where the Ca²⁺ wave mechanism specifically selects mid-cluster scissions?
+
+**Context:** Remote heartbeat run 16. Supabase/Slack blocked. Also applied backlogged EXPLORED entries for runs #14–15 (opener protocol). All committed locally, push blocked. This entry first reaches GitHub via run #19.
+
+**Findings:**
+
+U-shaped. Three regimes:
+
+*Low entanglement density (ancestral):* High CV. Few constrained scission sites — fracture is essentially random. High daughter-size variance.
+
+*Intermediate density (transitional PA clades):* CV minimum. The Ca²⁺ wave apoptosis cascade initiates preferentially at mid-cluster branch junctions — mechanically stressed interior points where branch contacts concentrate load. Geometric selection → consistent mid-sized daughters → low CV. This mechanism acts as a size-filter.
+
+*High density (advanced PA clades):* CV elevated again. Multiple competing fracture sites activate nearly simultaneously (stochastic race) + metabolic gradients (core hypoxia vs. peripheral normoxia) add independent variance. Multi-site events → unpredictable daughter sizes → CV rises.
+
+*Evolutionary signature.* The U-shape traced across the 5 PA clades should show: high → low → high. The minimum-CV clade maximized Ca²⁺ wave precision. That clade may also have the highest reproductive reliability — potentially the mechanism enabling macroscopic size crossing.
+
+**New questions generated:**
+- Does the U-shaped CV minimum correspond to the entanglement density at which macroscopic transition occurred? → Added to ACTIVE.
+- Is the Ca²⁺ mechanism directly documented in snowflake yeast or inferred from mammalian literature? → Added to ACTIVE.
